    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Eugenicists believed that certain \"races\" were inherently superior due to their physical characteristics, such as skin color, facial features, and body type. They claimed that these traits were determined by genetics and that individuals with \"undesirable\" characteristics, like darker skin or certain physical features, were less intelligent, less capable, and less deserving of resources. They also believed that the \"inferior\" races were overpopulating and threatening the purity of the \"superior\" races, which they believed was necessary for the survival of the fittest. They used pseudo-scientific theories like Social Darwinism and craniometry to support their claims, and argued that selective breeding and sterilization were necessary to maintain the racial hierarchy.",
