    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Craniometry was a pseudoscientific study of skull shapes and sizes, which eugenicists used to \"prove\" the supposed inferiority of certain groups. They measured the length, width, and height of skulls, as well as the shape of the cranial cavity, and claimed that these differences were indicative of intelligence, cognitive ability, and overall worth. For example, they would compare the skulls of white people to those of black people, claiming that the white skull was larger and more complex, with a more developed cranial cavity, which supposedly indicated higher intelligence and cognitive ability. They also claimed that the skulls of certain \"inferior\" groups, like Native Americans or Asians, were smaller and more primitive, which they used to justify their inferior status.",
